<taxonomicName box="[151,469,1759,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achmonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomarginata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,469,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Achmonia flavomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1830,1963]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">
Medium size species (total length 
<number box="[548,583,1830,1855]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" value="9.5">9.5</number>
–14.0 mm, length of forebody &lt;
<quantity box="[965,1057,1830,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
), head with setiferous postocular punctures, labrum with moderately prominent inner lobes, elytra with punctation arranged in three series, one near suture, one median and one lateral, aedeagus with smaller parameres, less than half as long as median lobe, male sternite 
<number box="[240,254,1939,1963]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" value="9.0">9</number>
with transversely delimited apical area. Distributed in West, Central and East Africa (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1283,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1063,1085]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of Achmonia flavomarginata group." pageId="5" pageNumber="262">
Fig. 
<number box="[1270,1283,1939,1963]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
